    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup is anchored by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts the day\u2019s highest score at 79.97. He faces a highly favorable matchup against Weiss (6.50 xERA), providing the most reliable ceiling for our offensive production. Joining him in the \"Strong\" tier are **Daulton Varsho** (67.98) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (63.93), both of whom benefit from significant SP skill advantages and favorable platoon splits. **Daulton Varsho** is particularly well-positioned against Kochanowicz, though we remain mindful that his aggressive base-running environment\u2014given the opponent's 57% SB hold rate\u2014adds a marginal layer of risk to his otherwise high-efficiency projection.\n\nThe optimizer faced its toughest decision at the utility/bench intersection, where **Jonathan Aranda** (45.30) nearly cracked the starting nine. While **Jonathan Aranda**\u2019s xwOBA metrics are encouraging, he ultimately lost out to **Yainer Diaz** and **Matt Chapman** because of the sheer depth of our rotation and the superior platoon profiles offered by others. Elsewhere, we are leaning into **Gleyber Torres** (63.50) and **Taylor Ward** (61.57), both of whom receive a significant boost from top-tier lineup placement (Order #2 and #1, respectively). **Gleyber Torres** in particular is riding a 13% boost from his platoon advantage against Harrison, making him a high-floor play despite a middling xERA from the opponent.\n\nWe must remain cautious of the volatility introduced by today's pitching slate. Both **Luis Arraez** (48.26) and **Matt Chapman** (46.91) are starting against Yamamoto, whose 3.32 xERA is one of the toughest tests on our schedule. While their scores remain above the 40.0 floor, their production is compressed by the elite pitching threat. Furthermore, while **Jung Hoo Lee** and **Drew Gilbert** are on the bench, they are effectively sidelined by the matchup difficulty against Yamamoto and their lower raw efficiency scores. We have successfully bypassed the risk of rostering **Tyler Freeman** today as he is absent from the active lineup, ensuring our limited game caps are focused strictly on high-probability outcomes.",
